    "7743608": {
      "title": "Correlation of the tibial tuberosity-trochlear groove distance with the Q-angle",
      "abstract": "Purpose ::: The Q-angle has been used for years to quantify lateralization of the patella. The tibial tuberosity–trochlea groove distance (TT–TG distance) was introduced to analyse patellar tracking. Does a significant correlation exist between these two parameters? Do other significant interrelations exist between the Q-angle/TT–TG distance, torsion of the femur and tibia, the frontal axis, overall leg length, gender, former patellar dislocation, BMI?"
    }
